    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-04T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-04T13:00:00-05:00" n="620"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d620">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 635.119/220</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SFJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-04T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SJH2">Stabler</persName> to
                    <persName>Robbins</persName>:</p>
                <p>Your March 2, 2 p.m. Matter given careful consideration. You may say to <persName
                        corresp="#p_NRS1">Naón</persName> in most informal manner that any proposals
                    coming from the Government of the Argentine Republic looking toward <pb
                        facs="0766" n="674" xml:id="pg_674"/> closer relationship between that
                    country and the United States will always receive most sympathetic
                    consideration.</p>
                <p>Department at a loss to understand what <persName corresp="#p_NRS1"
                        >Naón</persName> really has in mind …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
